    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 5 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER ES65-5 - DISASSEMBLE -
        MAINSHAFT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="9">
        <title>MAINSHAFT</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a suitable puller on reverse gear to remove the rear mainshaft bearing, thrust washer
                and reverse gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301328">Figure 28</hotlnk>). Remove the reverse gear caged bearings and 1st-reverse
                clutch gear.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301328" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301328" filename="../figg13/G1301328.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 28. Remove Rear Mainshaft Bearing, Thrust Washer and Reverse Gear</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Always wear safety glasses when pulling components off a shaft to protect your eyes from any
                        flying metal pieces.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a suitable puller to remove the 4th-5th speed synchronizer and the drive gear pocket
                bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301329">Figure 29</hotlnk>). Puller jaws should be positioned behind the clutch gear
                of the synchronizer.
                <emph type="bold">Do not pull on the brass ring.</emph>
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301329" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301329" filename="../figg13/G1301329.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 29. Remove 4th-5th Speed Synchronizer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 4th speed gear snap ring, then lift the 4th speed gear and thrust washer from the
                mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301330">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301330" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301330" filename="../figg13/G1301330.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 30. Lift 4th Speed Gear and Thrust Washer From Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a puller on 3rd speed gear to remove the 4th speed gear fluted sleeve (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301331">Figure 31</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301331" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301331" filename="../figg13/G1301331.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 31. Remove 4th Speed Gear Fluted Sleeve</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 2nd-3rd speed clutch gear snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301332">Figure 32</hotlnk>).
                <emph type="bold"></emph>
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301332" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301332" filename="../figg13/G1301332.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 32. Remove 2nd-3rd Speed Clutch Gear Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 2nd-3rd speed synchronizer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301333">Figure 33</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301333" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301333" filename="../figg13/G1301333.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 33. Remove 2nd-3rd Speed Synchronizer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 2nd-3rd speed clutch gear, then remove the 2nd speed gear from the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301334">Figure 34</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301334" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301334" filename="../figg13/G1301334.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 34. Remove 2nd Speed Gear From Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 2nd speed gear. Remove the caged needle bearings and 1st speed gear snap ring
                from the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301335">Figure 35</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301335" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301335" filename="../figg13/G1301335.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 35. Remove Caged Needle Bearings and 1st Speed Gear Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 1st speed gear thrust washer, 1st speed gear, and caged needle bearings (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301336">Figure 36</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301336" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301336" filename="../figg13/G1301336.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 36. Remove 1st Speed Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
